The paper discusses a framework for monitoring and managing HPC systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of Operational Data Analytics (ODA) and logical abstractions also suggests a focus on Performance Evaluation and Optimization (cs.PF) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions case studies targeting different aspects of HPC system management, which could fall under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
